Write a c program to find maximum number between two numbers using a pointer:

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
int main()
{
 int fno,sno,*ptr1=&fno,*ptr2=&sno;
 
   printf("\n\n Pointer : Find the maximum number between two numbers :\n"); 
   printf("------------------------------------------------------------\n");   
 
   printf(" Input the first number : ");
   scanf("%d", ptr1);
   printf(" Input the second  number : ");
   scanf("%d", ptr2); 


 if(*ptr1>*ptr2)
 {
  printf("\n\n %d is the maximum number.\n\n",*ptr1);
 }
 else
 {
  printf("\n\n %d is the maximum number.\n\n",*ptr2);
 }

}


Test cases:

Case 1:
Enter the first number:0
Enter the second number:4
4 is the maximum number

Case 2:
Enter the first number:5
Enter the second number:0
5 is the maximum number

Case 3:
Enter the first number:-3
Enter the second number:3
3 is the maximum number

Case 4:
Enter the first number:0
Enter the second number:0
0 is the maximum number




